Key Match Events: Namibia's Ruben Trumpelmann took 4 wickets in his first two overs.
Namibia dismissed Oman for 109 runs with 8 wickets in 18 overs.
Namibia chased Oman's 110-run target and needed 18 runs off the last over.
Namibia won the Super Over with Gerhard Erasmus and David Wiese scoring 21 runs.
Pre-Game Insights: Namibia captain Gerhard Erasmus won the toss and elected to bowl first.
Oman captain Aqib Ilyas chose to bat on a fresh wicket.
Namibia's Ruben Trumpelmann could not have asked for a better start to his T20 World Cup 2024 campaign.
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese was named the Player of the Match for his all-round heroics.
Aqib Ilyas praised Namibia's bowlers and acknowledged the quality of Ruben Trumpelmann's performance.
Gerhard Erasmus expressed happiness at breaking the duck in the tournament and highlighted the team's resilience.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Namibia's David Wiese took 3 wickets in the Super Over.
Oman's Bilal Khan conceded just 4 runs in the final over of the Super Over.
